WEBVTT

00:13.393 --> 00:15.854
You might not remember him, but...

00:16.479 --> 00:19.107
Stay there. I'm coming back.

00:19.190 --> 00:20.483
...he was a true knight.

00:22.277 --> 00:25.238
Different than other men. Yeah.

00:27.323 --> 00:29.159
He had a peaceable nature.

00:30.326 --> 00:32.996
Quiet and humble.

00:33.079 --> 00:35.832
A veteran of a hundred wars,
but an enemy to none.

00:39.377 --> 00:42.005
He always knew what was expected of him.

00:43.840 --> 00:45.216
He never complained.

00:47.260 --> 00:50.930
Even as he was dying, he just...

00:53.183 --> 00:54.934
He just got on with it.

00:58.063 --> 01:01.066
He meant to be a benefit
to those around him.

01:03.693 --> 01:05.235
It did not make him rich.

01:06.112 --> 01:10.116
He held no lands, sired no children.

01:11.826 --> 01:14.120
Off to Ashford to see a fair maid

01:14.204 --> 01:16.372
Heigh-ho, heigh-ho

01:16.456 --> 01:19.959
I'll make her my love
and we'll rest in the shade

01:20.043 --> 01:21.878
Heigh-ho, heigh-ho

01:21.961 --> 01:23.129
Come on, Dunk!

01:29.052 --> 01:31.554
He wanted for nothing but the open air.

01:32.514 --> 01:33.639
Hey.

01:33.723 --> 01:35.809
And a fire to warm his feet at.

01:44.275 --> 01:46.111
His skills as a warrior were...

01:47.612 --> 01:51.532
unsung, but he had
a chin cut from granite.

01:51.615 --> 01:54.077
-Come on.
-And he was a dogged fighter.

01:54.702 --> 01:56.663
He just, he kept on coming.

02:05.130 --> 02:09.133
I'll steal a sweet kiss
from the point of my blade

02:09.216 --> 02:11.719
Heigh-ho, heigh-ho

02:14.472 --> 02:16.474
Whoa! Whoa!

02:24.190 --> 02:27.235
House Florent, Ser Arlan
took service in your guard

02:27.318 --> 02:29.195
when your lord father lost his sight.

02:29.279 --> 02:32.115
I'll make her my love
and we'll rest in the shade

02:32.197 --> 02:34.450
Heigh-ho, heigh-ho

02:34.534 --> 02:36.202
House Hayford,

02:36.286 --> 02:39.747
Ser Arlan fought side by side
with your brothers at the Redgrass.

02:41.708 --> 02:45.211
His squire, his own nephew
was killed in the battle.

02:47.463 --> 02:49.215
House Tyrell...

02:50.258 --> 02:52.343
Ser Arlan often spoke
of his time in your service

02:52.427 --> 02:55.180
as his very finest.

02:56.389 --> 03:00.643
He said it was you, m'lord,
who told him that a hedge knight

03:00.727 --> 03:03.188
was the bridge between lords
and the smallfolk.

03:08.318 --> 03:09.694
I know him not, man.

03:12.280 --> 03:13.740
Was he a shit knight?

03:13.823 --> 03:15.241
He was not a shit knight.

03:15.325 --> 03:17.994
Well, he can't have been a very good one
if no one remembers him.

03:18.077 --> 03:19.871
Pick up your feet, come on.

03:19.954 --> 03:21.456
This is undignified, ser.

03:22.040 --> 03:25.084
So, hie back to camp
and leave me be, if it please you.

03:25.168 --> 03:26.961
I would not leave you, ser,

03:27.045 --> 03:29.130
not while you must
suffer your master dying

03:29.214 --> 03:30.757
over and over again.

03:30.840 --> 03:32.550
Though it does not seem like these lords

03:32.634 --> 03:34.302
are even listening to you.

03:35.136 --> 03:36.930
Nothing I can do about that.

03:37.639 --> 03:39.557
You are a knight of the realm, ser.

03:40.225 --> 03:41.893
You can say fuck their permission.

03:41.976 --> 03:44.187
Ride into the lists,
call out Longthorn Tyrell,

03:44.270 --> 03:46.481
and turn his arsehole into a lance-hole.

03:48.107 --> 03:49.733
That's enough now.

03:49.817 --> 03:53.238
Why do you treat these royal lapdogs
like they're your betters?

03:53.321 --> 03:56.991
They are my betters.
You're too brazen for your own good.

03:58.409 --> 04:00.328
Ser Arlan was a great knight.

04:01.162 --> 04:02.705
Someone will remember him.

04:08.086 --> 04:09.254
Hey. Who's come?

04:09.337 --> 04:11.547
Can't you see the banners, you giant cunt?

04:21.432 --> 04:24.811
Perhaps I should go back,
ser, check on the camp.

04:24.894 --> 04:26.980
Make sure no thieves
have been nosing about.

04:28.898 --> 04:30.441
Aye. I have an idea.

04:30.525 --> 04:32.568
Can I have your sword
to run people off with?

04:32.652 --> 04:34.654
-Or a mace?
-You have a knife.

04:34.737 --> 04:36.072
That's enough.

04:36.155 --> 04:38.283
You'd best be here when I come back.

04:38.366 --> 04:41.369
Rob me, and I'll hunt you down, with dogs.

04:41.452 --> 04:43.579
-You don't have dogs.
-I'll get some.

04:43.663 --> 04:44.789
Where?

04:58.845 --> 05:04.017
Our Lord of Ashford
humbly welcomes the great and honorable

05:04.100 --> 05:08.479
Baelor Targaryen,
firstborn son of King Daeron the Good.

05:10.064 --> 05:13.526
Prince of Dragonstone,
Hand of the King...

05:15.278 --> 05:17.613
and heir to the Iron Throne.

05:19.490 --> 05:21.784
And his brother, Maekar.

05:21.868 --> 05:23.077
My Lord of Ashford.

05:23.161 --> 05:25.288
It's a great honor to receive Your Grace.

05:25.371 --> 05:26.622
It's a great honor to be received.

05:26.706 --> 05:28.416
My daughter, Gwin.

05:37.592 --> 05:40.094
Boy, stop gaping. See to my horse.

05:41.846 --> 05:43.806
I'm not a stable boy, m'lord.

05:45.224 --> 05:46.768
Not clever enough?

05:50.313 --> 05:51.981
Well, if you can't manage horses,

05:52.065 --> 05:54.650
then fetch me some wine
and a pretty wench.

05:55.693 --> 05:59.781
Oh, m'lord pardons.
I'm no serving man, either.

06:02.492 --> 06:04.660
I have the honor to be a knight.

06:07.121 --> 06:09.290
Oh. Well...

06:10.875 --> 06:12.835
knighthood has fallen on sad days.

06:19.217 --> 06:20.593
Whoa, whoa. Whoa, whoa.

06:20.676 --> 06:22.553
-Move away!
-Easy.

06:22.637 --> 06:24.389
Easy now, come on.

06:24.472 --> 06:27.100
Come on. Yeah, it's okay. It's okay.

06:32.522 --> 06:33.898
There you are, girl.

06:35.525 --> 06:37.110
Far too many people around.

06:37.193 --> 06:38.945
I agree.

06:39.028 --> 06:41.614
Where the fuck am I meant
to put all these horses?

06:41.697 --> 06:43.866
The pretty ones are always temperamental.

06:44.534 --> 06:47.161
Ah, she just got a bit excited,
that's all.

06:47.245 --> 06:49.497
He meant the princeling, not the palfrey.

06:52.625 --> 06:53.960
Excuse me, m'lords.

06:54.919 --> 06:56.712
I'm Ser Duncan the Tall.

06:56.796 --> 06:58.589
Well met.
I'm Ser Roland Crakehall,

06:58.673 --> 07:01.008
and this is my sworn brother,
Ser Donnel of Duskendale.

07:01.092 --> 07:02.468
Gods, boy.

07:02.552 --> 07:04.554
Do you ride your horse into battle
or does it ride you?

07:04.637 --> 07:06.472
Forgive Ser Roland.

07:06.556 --> 07:10.017
It's not often he must look up
to cast his eyes down.

07:10.101 --> 07:11.811
Yes, yes, I'm quite the rascal.

07:12.353 --> 07:13.729
Now, tell me, Ser Duncan,

07:13.813 --> 07:15.898
is there a proper place
to shit around here?

07:16.899 --> 07:18.443
Not really, no.

07:22.947 --> 07:26.409
A man of such birth has never deigned
to disturb his arsehole with hay.

07:27.326 --> 07:29.579
He'll deign before
the week is out, I'd wager.

07:30.872 --> 07:32.582
Where are you from, man?

07:32.664 --> 07:33.916
You don't smell House-bred.

07:35.543 --> 07:38.087
-No place, really.
-I know it.

07:38.962 --> 07:40.465
My family's from there.

07:40.548 --> 07:42.967
You're not a Darklyn of Duskendale?

07:43.968 --> 07:45.928
We were crabbers at Duskendale.

07:46.012 --> 07:47.763
Far back as it goes.

07:49.140 --> 07:50.516
Ser Donnel?

07:52.602 --> 07:55.646
May I ask, ser, how the son of a crabber

07:55.730 --> 07:58.649
came to have the honor of being a knight
in the Kingsguard?

07:59.984 --> 08:01.694
Same way we became crabbers.

08:06.574 --> 08:07.909
"Same way we became..."

08:07.992 --> 08:10.119
Are you Baelor Targaryen?

08:11.662 --> 08:12.580
No.

08:12.663 --> 08:14.499
Then would you move
the fuck out of the way?

08:14.582 --> 08:16.959
Yeah. Yeah. Of course. Apologies.

08:18.586 --> 08:20.296
Sorry.

08:21.005 --> 08:23.508
The princes be needing
their fucking hands washed!

08:23.591 --> 08:25.676
I'm on my way, ma'am.

08:30.097 --> 08:32.140
Move! A carriage is comin' through!

08:55.623 --> 08:58.709
The spring rains have swollen
many of our streams.

08:58.793 --> 09:00.962
Perhaps the young princes
have just been delayed?

09:01.045 --> 09:02.338
Fuck me.

09:02.421 --> 09:04.549
"Delayed." They're not delayed.

09:04.632 --> 09:06.509
Do not curse our gracious host.

09:06.592 --> 09:08.594
I said "fuck me," not "fuck him."

09:08.678 --> 09:12.181
It's not his fault Father bade us
attend this miserable circus.

09:12.890 --> 09:14.892
Might we discuss this another time?

09:14.976 --> 09:16.519
I say we go hunting.

09:16.602 --> 09:18.563
Daeron has done this before.

09:19.647 --> 09:21.524
You should not have commanded him
to enter the lists.

09:23.276 --> 09:24.485
The prince's sons are missing.

09:25.403 --> 09:27.321
You'd be more concerned
if it was your son, I wager.

09:27.405 --> 09:29.198
-Oh.
-Probably dead.

09:30.199 --> 09:32.618
-Dead?
-Wars have started for less.

09:37.540 --> 09:39.000
You're big and stupid.

09:44.589 --> 09:46.424
They have only been missing a day.

09:47.550 --> 09:50.344
No doubt, Ser Roland will turn him up
and Aegon along with him.

09:51.012 --> 09:52.930
When the tourney is over, perhaps.

09:53.014 --> 09:54.682
Daeron belongs on a tourney field

09:54.765 --> 09:57.476
no more than Aerys or Rhaegel.

09:57.560 --> 09:59.937
By which you mean he'd sooner
ride a whore than a horse.

10:00.021 --> 10:01.606
That is not what I said.

10:05.151 --> 10:07.862
I do not need to be reminded
of my son's failings.

10:07.945 --> 10:10.406
He can change.
He will change, gods be damned.

10:10.489 --> 10:13.075
Or I swear, I'll see him dead.

10:15.953 --> 10:17.121
You.

10:17.955 --> 10:20.875
Who are you?
What do you mean by spying on us?

10:22.877 --> 10:24.128
Show yourself.

10:29.550 --> 10:33.429
My Lords, I do apologize
for my interruption. I...

10:36.557 --> 10:38.184
I have asked Ser Manfred Dondarrion

10:38.267 --> 10:41.020
to vouch for me so that I might
enter the lists,

10:41.103 --> 10:43.147
-but he has refused to do so.
-Who?

10:44.231 --> 10:45.358
What the fuck is going on?

10:45.441 --> 10:48.569
We are the intruders here, brother.
Come closer, ser.

10:50.321 --> 10:52.448
And others, too.

10:53.407 --> 10:57.244
You see, they say they know not
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

10:57.328 --> 11:00.081
But he served them. I swear it.

11:00.164 --> 11:01.999
I have his sword and shield.

11:02.875 --> 11:04.585
Sword and shield do not make a knight.

11:04.669 --> 11:05.670
Mm?

11:08.881 --> 11:11.342
Unless you have better proof
to support what you say.

11:11.425 --> 11:13.969
-Some writing or--
-Do you remember him, Your Grace?

11:16.722 --> 11:18.641
It was many years ago.

11:18.724 --> 11:20.267
You may have forgotten.

11:24.438 --> 11:26.023
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

11:28.693 --> 11:30.444
He never won a tourney that I know.

11:31.779 --> 11:33.114
But he never shamed himself, either.

11:33.197 --> 11:34.824
Yes, ser.

11:34.907 --> 11:36.867
I mean, no. No, he didn't.

11:36.951 --> 11:40.454
He overthrew Lord Stokeworth
in the melee at King's Landing

11:40.538 --> 11:42.790
and years before,
he unhorsed the Grey Lion himself.

11:42.873 --> 11:45.084
He told me of that many a time.

11:46.877 --> 11:49.588
Then, you will recall
the Grey Lion's true name,

11:50.506 --> 11:51.757
I have no doubt.

12:00.224 --> 12:02.518
Ser Damon Lannister.

12:02.601 --> 12:05.146
The Grey Lion,
he's Lord of Casterly Rock now.

12:05.229 --> 12:06.897
So he is.

12:06.981 --> 12:08.899
And enters the lists upon the morrow.

12:08.983 --> 12:11.694
How can you possibly remember
some fucking hedge knight

12:11.777 --> 12:15.322
who chanced to unhorse
Damon Lannister 16 years ago?

12:15.406 --> 12:17.825
I make it a practice to learn
all I can of my foes.

12:17.908 --> 12:20.286
And why would you deign
to joust with a hedge knight?

12:20.369 --> 12:22.621
It was many years past, at Storm's End.

12:22.705 --> 12:26.584
Lord Baratheon held a hastilude
to celebrate the birth of a grandson.

12:26.667 --> 12:29.086
The lots made Ser Arlan
my opponent in the first tilt.

12:29.754 --> 12:32.256
We broke four lances
before I finally unhorsed him.

12:32.339 --> 12:33.507
It was seven.

12:38.053 --> 12:39.764
I believe.

12:39.847 --> 12:41.348
Tales grow in the telling, I know.

12:43.726 --> 12:47.605
Do not think ill of your old master,
but it was four lances only, I fear.

12:47.688 --> 12:49.398
As you say, Your Grace.

12:49.482 --> 12:51.358
It was four. I do apologize.

12:51.442 --> 12:53.819
The old man, Ser Arlan, he used to say

12:53.903 --> 12:56.822
that I was thick as a castle wall
and slow as an aurochs.

12:56.906 --> 12:58.491
No harm was done, ser. Rise.

13:01.452 --> 13:04.997
You gave him back his horse and armor
and took no ransom.

13:06.165 --> 13:09.168
Ser Arlan often told me that
you were the soul of chivalry...

13:09.251 --> 13:10.503
-Ugh.
-...and that one day,

13:10.586 --> 13:13.672
the Seven Kingdoms
would be safe in your hands.

13:13.756 --> 13:16.050
Not for many years yet, I pray.

13:16.133 --> 13:19.094
No, I did not mean
that the King should--

13:19.178 --> 13:20.429
You wish to enter the lists.

13:20.513 --> 13:21.847
Is that it?

13:22.848 --> 13:24.225
-Yes.
-The decision rests

13:24.308 --> 13:27.102
with the master of the games,
but I see no reason to deny you.

13:27.186 --> 13:28.771
As you say, m'lord.

13:30.272 --> 13:31.273
Mm.

13:32.316 --> 13:33.150
Your Grace--

13:33.234 --> 13:36.278
Very well, ser, You are grateful.
Now, fuck off!

13:36.362 --> 13:38.155
You must forgive my brother, ser.

13:38.239 --> 13:41.242
His sons went astray on the way here,
and he fears for them.

13:41.325 --> 13:42.701
Of course.

13:43.911 --> 13:45.287
I trust they will not be found dead.

13:57.174 --> 13:58.175
Ser.

14:00.886 --> 14:02.721
You are not of Ser Arlan's blood?

14:04.640 --> 14:05.850
No, I am not.

14:07.142 --> 14:10.437
By law, only a trueborn son
is entitled to inherit a knight's arms.

14:10.521 --> 14:12.815
You must needs find a new device, ser.

14:13.607 --> 14:14.859
A sigil of your own.

14:16.652 --> 14:17.653
I will.

14:19.572 --> 14:21.240
Thank you again, Your Grace.

14:23.242 --> 14:26.287
I will fight bravely. You'll see.

14:32.751 --> 14:33.794
It's this way.

14:33.878 --> 14:35.129
You are no knight.

14:40.551 --> 14:42.636
You are Florian the Fool.

14:42.720 --> 14:44.680
I am, my lady.

14:46.140 --> 14:48.017
As great a fool as ever lived.

14:51.770 --> 14:54.481
And as great a knight as well!

14:59.236 --> 15:01.405
A fool and a knight.

15:02.323 --> 15:04.700
I have never heard of such a thing.

15:04.783 --> 15:06.535
Sweet lady.

15:06.619 --> 15:09.330
All men are fools,
and all men are knights...

15:10.331 --> 15:11.624
...where women are concerned.

15:25.262 --> 15:26.513
Hello there.

15:28.807 --> 15:30.851
And one for last night.

15:31.936 --> 15:32.978
That was great.

15:33.062 --> 15:35.230
How'd you do the fire tricks?

15:35.314 --> 15:36.565
Oh.

15:41.695 --> 15:42.738
Is it pollen?

15:42.821 --> 15:45.366
Yeah, we collect it on the way.

15:48.827 --> 15:50.871
I've never seen such giant puppets.

15:50.955 --> 15:52.206
Do you make them yourself?

15:52.289 --> 15:55.334
My uncle builds them, but I paint.

15:56.418 --> 15:58.003
Could you paint something for me?

15:59.004 --> 16:02.758
I have the coin to pay. I just...

16:05.052 --> 16:07.179
I need to paint
something over the chalice.

16:07.262 --> 16:09.848
Well, what would you want?

16:13.852 --> 16:14.937
I...

16:15.020 --> 16:17.231
I don't actually know.

16:17.314 --> 16:18.315
I...

16:19.483 --> 16:21.652
Sorry, you must think me a fool.

16:21.735 --> 16:24.363
All men are fools,
and all men are knights.

16:26.323 --> 16:27.324
Mm.

16:32.913 --> 16:33.956
Yeah.

16:36.083 --> 16:38.377
The gray is a bit drab.

16:38.460 --> 16:39.461
Aye.

16:40.963 --> 16:44.049
Yeah, the field should be
the color of sunset

16:44.925 --> 16:47.428
'cause the old man
always liked sunsets and...

16:47.511 --> 16:49.680
An elm tree. A big one.

16:49.763 --> 16:52.474
Like the one by the river
with the brown trunk

16:52.558 --> 16:54.935
and the green branches.

16:55.019 --> 16:57.980
Aye. An elm tree, that would serve.

16:58.981 --> 17:00.899
But with a shooting star above.

17:01.900 --> 17:03.944
-Could you do that?
-Mm-hmm.

17:05.487 --> 17:08.699
Thank you, I'm Ser Duncan the Tall.

17:10.450 --> 17:12.494
I'm Tanselle.

17:12.578 --> 17:15.872
The boys used to call me
Tanselle Too-Tall.

17:17.332 --> 17:19.584
You're not too tall.
I mean, you're just right for...

17:22.629 --> 17:23.839
For?

17:24.547 --> 17:26.175
Puppets.

17:27.426 --> 17:28.927
Yeah, puppets.

17:30.179 --> 17:31.263
Okay, I'll...

17:31.346 --> 17:33.307
-Wait. The shield.
-Yes, sorry.

17:33.390 --> 17:34.516
-Yes, the shield.
-Yeah.

17:34.600 --> 17:35.934
Was that ill-handled?

17:36.560 --> 17:39.104
-Hm?
-The puppet girl.

17:40.230 --> 17:41.231
Oh.

17:42.691 --> 17:45.319
It didn't feel well-handled.

17:46.570 --> 17:48.447
She is painting your shield.

17:48.530 --> 17:49.865
Yeah, for pay.

17:52.284 --> 17:54.161
You are both gigantic.

17:58.832 --> 18:00.167
Is that promising?

18:01.418 --> 18:02.628
It's a...

18:04.213 --> 18:05.506
commonality.

18:07.174 --> 18:09.676
Right, yeah. Commonality.

18:11.303 --> 18:12.346
I don't know.

18:18.060 --> 18:19.686
Do you think I'll ever make
a knight one day?

18:20.687 --> 18:22.815
Sure, why not? You're a likely lad.

18:22.898 --> 18:24.900
I'm a bit puny.

18:24.983 --> 18:27.319
-You'll grow.
-Even for my age.

18:27.402 --> 18:29.029
Everyone's always told me so.

18:32.616 --> 18:34.868
Everyone's always told me I was stupid.

18:43.877 --> 18:44.878
And?

18:45.921 --> 18:46.922
Hm?

18:47.965 --> 18:49.508
-Hm? What?
-What?

18:50.801 --> 18:53.679
What did you do when people
said you were stupid, ser?

18:55.222 --> 18:56.849
What business is that of yours?

18:57.391 --> 18:59.143
My problems are my own.

18:59.226 --> 19:00.686
I thought...

19:00.769 --> 19:02.187
Aren't you trying to help me?

19:02.271 --> 19:04.314
Help you what? Grow?

19:04.398 --> 19:05.774
Yes! Hedge knight, you.

19:08.443 --> 19:10.696
What is this piss froth? I need muscle.

19:11.822 --> 19:13.782
Will you heed my call to war?

19:14.908 --> 19:16.243
Aha! Good.

19:16.326 --> 19:17.744
Go! Get up, come.

19:17.828 --> 19:20.080
Ready!

19:22.082 --> 19:25.252
Hey! Dry those palms,
you clam-handed cunt.

19:25.335 --> 19:27.421
We're not in your sister's chambers now.

19:27.504 --> 19:29.131
Ready?

19:31.383 --> 19:33.760
-Go!
-Pull!

19:34.636 --> 19:37.472
If we lose this,
I'll be drowning your firstborn!

19:37.556 --> 19:39.266
-Come on!
-Pull! Pull!

19:39.349 --> 19:42.352
Pull, you cunt-strapped dandelions!

19:50.694 --> 19:52.654
I'll be back. I'll be back! I'll be back.

19:52.738 --> 19:54.448
Lyonel! What are you doing?

19:54.531 --> 19:56.325
-I'm thirsty.
-Lyonel!

19:57.993 --> 19:59.453
Pull!

20:01.788 --> 20:03.207
I'm thirsty, cunt.

20:05.876 --> 20:07.878
I'm thirsty!

20:11.673 --> 20:12.758
Looking good.

20:20.098 --> 20:22.893
Fucking pull!

20:51.755 --> 20:54.132
-You do good work.
-None better.

20:56.802 --> 20:58.387
I need some armor on the morrow.

20:59.805 --> 21:02.849
Gorget, greaves, and great helm.

21:02.933 --> 21:04.309
Are you jousting or working?

21:05.519 --> 21:06.520
Both, perhaps.

21:10.482 --> 21:13.360
You're a big one,
though I've armored bigger.

21:17.489 --> 21:20.409
I have some pieces
in the wagon that might do.

21:20.492 --> 21:23.704
Nothing prettied up
with gold or silver, like.

21:23.787 --> 21:26.957
Just good steel, strong and plain.

21:27.040 --> 21:31.628
I make helms that look like helms,
not winged pigs and fancy foreign fruit.

21:33.422 --> 21:36.300
But mine'll serve you better
if you take a lance in the face.

21:36.383 --> 21:39.344
That's all I want. How much?

21:39.428 --> 21:42.389
Eight hundred stag,
for I'm feeling kindly.

21:42.472 --> 21:43.849
Eight hundred?

21:45.851 --> 21:48.312
Perhaps I could trade you some
armor made for a smaller man.

21:48.395 --> 21:50.647
A half helm, a mail hauberk.

21:50.731 --> 21:53.734
Steely Pate sells only his own work.

22:08.457 --> 22:09.791
I could make use of the metal.

22:10.917 --> 22:14.379
If it's not too rusted,
I'll take it and armor you for...

22:16.048 --> 22:17.215
600.

22:18.925 --> 22:21.136
I only have two stags.

22:21.219 --> 22:23.055
Buys you a day.

22:26.725 --> 22:28.226
Send your squire along with the rest,

22:28.310 --> 22:30.520
or else I'll sell me wares
to the next man.

22:31.897 --> 22:33.607
You'll get it all back, I swear it.

22:34.816 --> 22:36.485
I mean to be a champion here.

22:36.568 --> 22:37.694
Do you, now?

22:39.696 --> 22:41.615
And the others all came just...

22:42.616 --> 22:43.784
just to cheer you on?

23:03.053 --> 23:05.680
Is there any measure of a fool
I fail to meet?

23:12.187 --> 23:16.191
If I win, I'll come back
and buy you again.

23:16.274 --> 23:17.609
I promise.

23:20.862 --> 23:22.489
Best girl.

23:40.298 --> 23:41.633
That's for her.

23:44.010 --> 23:46.430
See she has some oats tonight, yeah?

23:54.312 --> 23:55.772
And an apple, too.

24:08.201 --> 24:09.953
No turning back now, I suppose.

24:17.961 --> 24:20.464
You know, the old man
lived nigh on 60 years

24:20.547 --> 24:23.049
-and was never a champion.
-There's a bug in my cider.

24:24.676 --> 24:27.721
If I could call myself
a champion of Ashford Meadow...

24:28.930 --> 24:30.515
even for an hour...

24:32.142 --> 24:35.145
maybe some great house
might take me into its service.

24:37.189 --> 24:39.232
Perhaps even House Targaryen.

24:41.067 --> 24:43.820
You suppose the dragon house
employs many hedge knights, ser?

24:44.821 --> 24:46.781
Enough of that.

24:46.865 --> 24:48.992
I'll have you know
Ser Donnel of the Kingsguard

24:49.075 --> 24:50.869
is but the son of a crabber.

24:52.037 --> 24:53.622
Ser Donnel?

24:53.705 --> 24:55.624
-Of Duskendale?
-Yeah.

24:55.707 --> 24:58.543
His father owns half
the crabbing fleets in Westeros.

24:59.753 --> 25:00.837
What?!

25:02.923 --> 25:04.132
How would you know?

25:05.050 --> 25:06.718
I like fishing.

25:12.057 --> 25:13.475
It's time!

25:14.893 --> 25:16.061
Right, come on, let's go.

25:16.144 --> 25:18.230
Come on, pick your feet up. Let's go.

25:23.318 --> 25:24.736
Wait for me!

25:33.286 --> 25:34.788
Ser Duncan!

25:34.871 --> 25:36.081
Ser Duncan!

25:37.832 --> 25:39.543
Oh.

25:39.626 --> 25:41.211
-You alright?
-Yeah.

26:18.039 --> 26:21.126
For the new gods and old!

26:34.055 --> 26:35.265
Lance!

26:38.810 --> 26:41.104
Shield, and lance.

26:47.902 --> 26:48.903
Helmet!

26:50.780 --> 26:52.866
Hey, who's that?

26:52.949 --> 26:55.410
Prince Valarr, Baelor's son.

26:56.620 --> 26:58.330
-Second in line to the throne.
-Shield!

26:58.413 --> 27:00.248
He's the favorite, I'd wager.

27:00.332 --> 27:01.791
I'll take that bet, ser.

27:20.477 --> 27:23.396
Lord Ashford fucks his sheep!

27:43.708 --> 27:46.086
Come on! Whoo!

27:51.800 --> 27:54.094
Squire! Lance, lance, lance!

28:10.610 --> 28:12.612
Ser. Put me down, ser.

28:22.622 --> 28:23.832
Hyah! Hyah!

28:35.885 --> 28:36.928
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

29:07.876 --> 29:09.169
Die!

29:09.252 --> 29:11.921
Do you yield, Blackfyre bastards?!

29:17.427 --> 29:19.012
Splendid riding tonight.

29:21.890 --> 29:24.225
Mm, the part with the fish was disgusting.

29:30.607 --> 29:32.734
Something the matter, ser?

29:37.197 --> 29:41.993
Do great knights live in the hedges
and die by the side of a muddy road?

29:46.372 --> 29:47.665
I think not.

29:51.544 --> 29:54.297
Ser Arlan wasn't gifted
with sword or lance,

29:54.380 --> 30:00.136
and he drank, and he whored,
and he was a hard man to know.

30:03.681 --> 30:05.225
He made no friends, either.

30:06.267 --> 30:09.312
He lived nigh on 60 years
and never was a champion.

30:10.855 --> 30:13.733
Mm, what chance do I have? Truly?

30:17.278 --> 30:18.613
But he was good to me.

30:24.410 --> 30:25.995
I wasn't his family...

30:27.288 --> 30:28.915
but he kept me like we were.

30:33.878 --> 30:35.922
He raised me to be an honorable man.

30:39.759 --> 30:41.511
And all these

30:42.971 --> 30:46.015
noble lords can't even remember his name.

30:49.102 --> 30:51.312
His name was Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

30:53.189 --> 30:54.816
And I am his legacy.

30:56.109 --> 30:57.735
On the morrow...

30:59.487 --> 31:01.531
we will show them
what his hand has wrought.
